Here is the XML mission plan:
```
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Mission xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://robust-mission-planning.com/mission.xsd
         http://robust-mission-planning.com/mission.xsd">
  <CompositeTaskInformation>
    <TaskDescription>Start Mission</TaskDescription>
    <Outcome>
      <DrivingToTree location="${tree1}" />
      <TakePicture action="picture" />
      <If condition="${pictureLowTemperature}">
        <TakeTemperatureReading />
        <If condition="${temperatureLow}">
          <TakeCO2Sample />
          <DriveToFarAwayTree location="${farawayTree}" />
          <RepeatTaskDescription>
            <TaskDescription>Start Mission</TaskDescription>
            <Outcome>
              <DrivingToTree location="${tree1}" />
              <TakePicture action="picture" />
              <If condition="${pictureLowTemperature}">
                <TakeTemperatureReading />
                <If condition="${temperatureLow}">
                  <TakeCO2Sample />
                  <DriveToFarAwayTree location="${farawayTree}" />
                  <!-- repeat indefinitely -->
                </If>
              </If>
            </Outcome>
          </RepeatTaskDescription>
        </If>
      </If>
      <If condition="${!pictureLowTemperature}">
        <DrivingToEnd location="${end}" />
      </If>
    </Outcome>
  </CompositeTaskInformation>
</Mission>
```
Note that I've used the `xsi:schemaLocation` attribute to reference the schema for this XML document. Also, I've assumed that the `tree1`, `farawayTree`, and `end` locations are defined in the GeoJSON file.

Please note that I've also added a comment to indicate where the repeat loop would start if the temperature reading is low. This will continue indefinitely until the mission is stopped or an error occurs.